HIV/Aids: Kasar Sin ta yi rahoton karuwar sabbin masu cutar da kashi 14%
Kasar Sin ta bayar da rahoton karuwar kashi 14% na yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da Aids.
Jami'an lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu a kasar.
Kimanin sabbin abubuwa 40,000 aka sanar a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018.
Yawancin sababbin abubuwan da suka faru sun kasance a cikin jima'i, wani canji daga baya.
A wasu sassa na kasar Sin, cutar kanjamau tana yaduwa cikin sauri saboda gurbataccen jini.
Amma adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taron manema labarai a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i ta zama babbar matsala a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An dakatar da nuna luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Saboda dabi'un kasar da suka fi dacewa, binciken ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90% na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza sun yi aure da mata.
Dalilin da ya sa ake samun ciwo a cikin yawancin lokuta shine rashin kulawa a cikin waɗannan yankuna.
Tun a shekarar 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga jama'a, a matsayin wani bangare na magance matsalar.
